A world leader in gasses, technologies and services for Industry and Health,
Air Liquide is present in 78 countries with approximately 64,500 employees and
serves more than 3.8 million customers and patients. Oxygen, nitrogen and
hydrogen are essential small molecules for life, matter and energy. They
embody Air Liquide’s scientific territory and have been at the core of the
company’s activities since its creation in 1902.

Air Liquide Healthcare Australia is a leading and dedicated supplier of
medical gasses, homecare and sleep services. We specialise in respiratory
diseases and have a strong reputation in sleep diagnostics and CPAP therapy.

** The role **

Covering our ** Newstead, QLD ** clinic, as the Retail Consultant / CPAP
Therapy Consultant, you are employed on a part time basis working 22.8 hours a
week (3 days).  

Our clinics' primary objective is to assist our clients/patients with tailored
end-to-end solutions, treatments and management of obstructive sleep apnea.

  
** How will you CONTRIBUTE and GROW? **

  * Full and comprehensive training provided 
  * Being the first point of contact for our new/existing clients 
  * Interactions are either over the counter and/or phone and emails 
  * Providing advice on CPAP equipment, set-ups and on-going services 
  * Interacting with physicians, hospitals and medical service providers 
  * Upsell of our products and services 
  * Maintaining and sterilising clinic equipment 
  * Processing orders and clinic stocktake 

** Are you a MATCH? **

  * Previous experience in a retail, healthcare or sales 
  * Effective communication skills 
  * Ability to work autonomously in clinic 
  * Sound customer service experience: customer lifecycle stages 
  * Computer skills and confidence in using google suites 
  * Interest in CPAP therapy/sleep medicine 
  * Strong organisational and administrational skills 

** We offer: **

  * Part-time permanent role at 22.8 hours per week (3 days) 
  * Effective onboarding and training to ensure a smooth transition into the role 
  * Autonomy: whilst striving towards the teams objectives 
  * Salary Continuance Insurance 
  * Local and Global opportunities at our Air Liquide Group 
  * For more information please visit https://sleepsolutionsaustralia.com/about-us 

** APPLY NOW! **

As part of the pre-employment process, potential employees are required to
undertake background checks applicable to the requirements of the position
i.e., reference checks, medical check, police check, and Australian working
rights confirmation.

** About Air Liquide **   
A world leader in gases, technologies and services for Industry and Health,
Air Liquide is present in 78 countries with approximately 64,500 employees and
serves more than 3.8 million customers and patients. Oxygen, nitrogen and
hydrogen are essential small molecules for life, matter and energy. They
embody Air Liquide’s scientific territory and have been at the core of the
